ectricity customers across the us southern company gas serves utility customers in seven states southern company owns the following companies alabama power  operating company based in birmingham serves the southern twothirds of alabama georgia power  operating company based in atlanta serves all of georgia except four mostly rural counties gulf power  operating company based in pensacola florida serves most of the florida panhandle mississippi power  operating company based in gulfport serves the mississippi gulf coast southern company services  originally named southern services inc  birmingham alabama  common services southern linc  cellular telephone provider  atlanta georgia southern nuclear  engineering and operations for nuclear power plants  birmingham alabama southern company is the majority owner and operator of the farley hatch and vogtle nuclear power plants southern company generation  fossil and hydro operations  birmingham alabama southern power  wholesale power generation  atlanta georgia southern telecom  wholesale fiber optic communications and data services  atlanta georgia southern company gas  serves gas utility customers and operates natural gas pipelines  atlanta georgia powersecure  distributed infrastructure technologies  wake forest north carolina historyedit southern company can be traced back to  when southeastern power  light was formed as a holding company for alabama traction light and power formed  the immediate forerunner of alabama power later that year it formed mississippi power as a subsidiary with gulf power following in  in  it merged with georgia power formed  in  southeastern power  light merged into the commonwealth  southern corporation the new system included five northern companies and six southern companies however in the late s commonwealth  southern was dissolved to meet the public utility holding company act of  four of the southern companies—alabama power georgia power gulf power and mississippi power—were deemed to be an integrated system and thus were allowed to remain under common ownership a new holding company southern company was incorporated in delaware on november   and moved to georgia in  the year  saw southern company’s first full year of operation in – the company was involved in the dixonyates contract with the atomic energy commission and the associated political controversy in  southern company became the first electric utility holding company in  years to diversify its operations by forming an unregulated subsidiary in january  southern energy inc began official operations as a global energy company growing to serve  countries on four continents on april   southern company completed the spinoff of southern energy as mirant corporation another southern company subsidiary—southern nuclear—began providing services in  to the systems nuclear power plants in  southern communications services began providing digital wireless communications services to southern companys subsidiaries and also began marketing these services to the public within the southeast as southern linc southern telecom a telecommunications subsidiary of southern company was founded in  southern telecom provides colocation and dark fiber optic lines to network businesses on january   southern company received final approval from the securities and exchange commission to form southern power a subsidiary to own manage and finance wholesale generating assets in the southeast the new subsidiary targets wholesale customers on july   southern company gas received certification from the georgia public service commission to enter the retail gas market after nearly four years of operations the company was sold and customers transferred to cobb emcs newly formed affiliate gas south in  southern company acquired powersecure a distributed energy infrastructure technologies company and agl resources which was renamed southern company gas as a result of the agl resources merger southern company doubled its customer base expanded its footprint and broadened the scope of its business by increasing its natural gas presence plant vogtleedit plant vogtle in georgia southern company and its partners are constructing two new units on this site by  southern company subsidiaries operate hydroelectric gas coal and nuclear generation sources to generate approximately  terawatthours of electricity in  coal represented  percent of the companys output followed by nuclear  and natural gas  renewable hydroelectric power represented  percent of southerns generation coalbased generation dropped significantly in  from an average of  between  and  in june  the united states department of energy awarded an  billion loan guarantee to facilitate the construction of two new nuclear reactors at plant vogtle near augusta georgia a southern company subsidiary georgia power owns  of the current  mw facility with coowners oglethorpe power  municipal electric authority of georgia  and the city of dalton  the plant is operated by georgia power the  billion construction project is scheduled to be completed by  and would double the plants capacity the construction of two  mw reactors has been hailed by energy secretary steven chu as the first new nuclear power plant to break ground in decades it is expected to create up to  jobs during the construction phase and  once operational however in march  westinghouse electric company who are building the plant filed for chapter  bankruptcy because of  billion of losses from its two us nuclear construction projects the us government had given  billion of loan guarantees on the financing of the four nuclear reactors being built in the us and it is expected a way forward to completing the plant can be agreed plant ratcliffeedit in september  the epa introduced new provisions regarding output of carbon emissions in new power facilities the proposed emission limit for new energy sources will be lbs of carbon dioxide per megawatt hour of electricity preemptively recogni